candidates.title: Expose sea-orm feature flags in sea-orm-migration
candidates.body:
Some features of the sea-query language are unavailable in migrations with the default feature flags, so we need to be able to enable them in sea-orm-migration.

## PR Info

- Closes N/A

## New Features
N/A

## Bug Fixes
If you have a column definition like this in your table create statement,
```rust
    .col(
        ColumnDef::new(Release::Date)
            .date()
            .default(Value::ChronoDate(None)),
    )
```
It would fail to compile, because `Value::ChronoDate` comes from `sea-query`, and is behind the `with-chrono` feature flag.

As a workaround, at least when using SQLite, `Value::String` can be used instead, but then the migration is not quite correct.

## Breaking Changes
This should not break anything.

## Changes
N/A

candidates.title: change: rename `core` crate to `service` in examples
candidates.body:
## PR Info
This pull request addresses the issue of naming conflicts with the 'core' crate in the project's examples. Currently, the 'core' crate causes issues when used in conjunction with certain macros that rely on the '::core::result::Result' or any item from the Rust '::core' namespace. This PR proposes renaming the 'core' crate to 'service' throughout the examples to resolve these conflicts and improve usability. 

## Changes
- Renamed the 'core' crate to 'service' in all example files.
- Updated references to the renamed crate in the documentation and code comments.

## Related Issue
- https://github.com/illicitonion/num_enum/issues/27

## Testing Done
I have tested only Axum example, but the rest should be working just fine.
